{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"7799524986617933876","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2012-06-07T02:30:00-07:00","updated":"2012-06-07T02:30:03-07:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2012/06/sf-brunch-at-brendas.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/7799524986617933876","title":"SF brunch at Brenda's","content":"<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-HIh4k78d_eM/T9BEo0A7yYI/AAAAAAAANt0/jEyIoX6upBk/s1600/photo+(71).JPG\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img alt=\"Brenda's shrimp and cheddar grits\" border=\"0\" height=\"500\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-HIh4k78d_eM/T9BEo0A7yYI/AAAAAAAANt0/jEyIoX6upBk/s1600/photo+(71).JPG\" title=\"Brenda's shrimp and cheddar grits\" width=\"500\" /></a></div>\nIt's been a while since I've had a good brunch, but then last week, while driving through San Francisco, we stopped at <a href=\"http://bit.ly/Kz6QrA\" target=\"_blank\">Brenda's</a> for some French soul food, and now I can't stop thinking about it! I ordered the&nbsp;sautéed&nbsp;shrimp and cheddar grits which were&nbsp;<i>amazing</i>. (Do you like grits? I know a lot of people who don't care for them, but I recently found out that I really like them.)<br />\n<br />\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nCHZ2ADVhKA/T9BEl8aIHKI/AAAAAAAANts/NefCefl-ADs/s1600/photo+(70).JPG\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img alt=\"brenda's french soul food\" border=\"0\" height=\"500\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nCHZ2ADVhKA/T9BEl8aIHKI/AAAAAAAANts/NefCefl-ADs/s1600/photo+(70).JPG\" title=\"brenda's french soul food\" width=\"500\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: left;\">\nThe last time I was at Brenda's, it was half the size. Now the space is airy and bright. One wall is covered entirely with these beautiful mirrors.</div>\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: left;\">\n<br /></div>\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-3QTATdjnn6s/T9BEqn4HEtI/AAAAAAAANt8/nvqnZA8i-Co/s1600/photo+%252872%2529.JPG\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img alt=\"brenda's watermelon sweet tea\" border=\"0\" height=\"500\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-3QTATdjnn6s/T9BEqn4HEtI/AAAAAAAANt8/nvqnZA8i-Co/s1600/photo+%252872%2529.JPG\" title=\"brenda's watermelon sweet tea\" width=\"500\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: left;\">\nOur whole table ordered the watermelon sweet tea and a plate of beignets. And while the beignets were good, the watermelon sweet tea was what really stood out. It's what I want to drink every day this summer—I need to find a recipe!&nbsp;</div>","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"0","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/7799524986617933876/comments"},"labels":["To Eat"]}